page.title: 05Traffic Survey, Chester Rd.
page.content:
{Traffic Survey On The Chester Road on {Monday the 10th June 1985 between {9.20a.m and 9.35a.m.
On Monday we did the same kind of survey but it was in the morning. I worked with Jonathan Stear again we did lorries and vans going south. There was fourty four. There was more in the second one we did because in the morning most people are going to work. There were a lot of cars going south because that is the way to Birmingham and a lot of people in Streetly work in Birmingham.
See page 6 for details.
